Dear RACS Families,

It is with deep sadness that we share the news that our 2014 RACS graduate, Diante Harring, recently passed away.

We are in the process of gathering more information and exploring ways in which we can support Diante‚Äôs family, friends, and classmates.

Diante will always be remembered as a kind, positive, and respectful young man who was loved by so many in the RACS community. Our heartfelt condolences go out to his family and friends. We will miss his warm smiling face dearly.

Mehmet Demirtas

post_text:
Attention ALL RACS Elementary Families,

There has been a schedule change for the Elementary Orientation date. The RACS elementary virtual Orientation/Welcome Back video link will be available to families on August 28th, 2020 by 1:00pm. We are so excited to meet our new families and to see all of our returning families soon.

A letter was sent to you in the mail on Thursday August 20th regarding the upcoming start of the 2020/2021 school year! This includes your welcome letter, supply list, school calendar, teacher assignment and if you chose our hybrid option, group assignments.

If you have questions you may reach out to our main office at 585-235-0135.

Best,
Deanna Wilkinson
Elementary Principal
Rochester Academy Charter School

post_text:
Today, June 19th (Juneteenth) is a very important day for African Americans and RACS stands together with our students and their families.

Why do we celebrate Juneteenth?

In 1865, two and a half years after the passage of the Emancipation Proclamation Union, General Gordon Granger announced federal orders in the city of Galveston, Texas that all slaves were free.

Please take this time to reflect on and teach your families about critical issues that caused discrimination against black people in the United States of America. You can find more information about Juneteeth at https://www.juneteenth.com/.

As you celebrate today, know that RACS is celebrating with you. #INTHISTOGETHER #ROC

It Is our pleasure to announce Asani and Joe as RACS award winners for Private Parochial League "Senior Athletes of the Year". Asani and Joe have shown dedication, commitment, and hard work to not only their athletic endeavors but also their academics. They were leaders in the classroom, on the field and courts, and we know that will continue for them in whatever fields they choose. Both of these students are examples of what can be done with determination and the desire to do well. This award is not one that is just handed out but one that is earned we cannot be happier for the two of them. #ROC #Congratulations Goodschoolsroc

Stay safe and connected!

post_text:
Attention RACS Elementary Families!

Our teachers have prepared additional instructional materials for students to use over the next several weeks.The learning packets will be available for parent pick-up next week at the Elementary Building .Staff will be set up at the RACS main entrance for pick-up from 11:00 am - 1:00 pm on Tuesday, 4/14 and Wednesday, 4/15.Staff will be taking precautions during pick-up by wearing masks and gloves. Parents will not need to exit their vehicles for the materials pick-up. You are welcome to bring your child along so we can wave from a distance. Please be on the look out for something special from our staff to all our RACS families. It will be posted on Dojo next week.

We miss you all so much!

Sincerely,

Mrs. Wilkinson--
Elementary Principal
